          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Seniors'</b><b> Security Act of 201</b><b>7</b></p> <p class="MsoNormal">This bill requires the use of&nbsp;a Consumer Price Index for Elderly Consumers (CPI-E) to calculate certain cost-of-living adjustments&nbsp;with respect to&nbsp;the Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance benefits program and certain other federal retirement benefits. The Department of Labor&nbsp;must prepare and publish the CPI-E for each calendar month.</p> <p>The bill&nbsp;also limits certain increases&nbsp;in&nbsp;Medicare premiums.</p>]]></text>
